      "type": "thought",
      "text": "The user is experiencing a BSOD with \"WHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR\". They want:\n\n1. Root cause analysis\n2. Fixability score using iFix\n3. Reliability assessment\n4. Whether they can safely improve PC temperature\n5. Component health assessment without stress testing\n6. Use PowerShell and Python tools\n\nSince I'm in plan mode (read-only), I can only research and plan. Let me:\n\n1. Research WHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR root causes\n2. Check if there's an \"iFix\" tool or if they mean something else\n3. Plan diagnostic steps using PowerShell and Python\n\nWHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR is typically hardware-related:\n- CPU overheating\n- CPU voltage issues\n- RAM failures\n- Motherboard issues\n- Overclocking instability\n\nI should search for information about this error and what tools are available in the system.\n\nLet me first understand what's available on their system and what \"iFix\" refers to.",
