      "code": "{\"query\": \"WHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR root cause analysis fixability 2024 2025\"}",
      "output": "{\n  \"search_id\": \"search_6eab7455ab1044c6a3dc3b991716ec9b\",\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.quora.com/How-do-I-fix-a-whea-uncorrectable-error\",\n      \"title\": \"How to fix a whea uncorrectable error - Quora\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"Something went wrong. Wait a moment and try again.\\n\\nTry again\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://mdrepairs.com/blog/whea-uncorrectable-error\",\n      \"title\": \"WHEA Uncorrectable Error Fix | Windows Blue Screen\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2026-04-08\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"This is one of several blue screen errors that can indicate storage problems. The good news is that some causes are fixable with basic troubleshooting. Overheating, outdated drivers, bad BIOS settings. The bad news? If the error keeps coming back, you’re probably looking at a hardware failure. And if your storage drive is the culprit, your data could be at risk.\\n\\nWe see computers with this error come through our data recovery lab regularly. Sometimes it’s a simple overheating issue and the customer fixes it by cleaning out dust. Other times, the drive has bad sectors spreading across the platters, and recovery is the only way to save the files. The key is figuring out which situation you’re in before you lose anything important.\\n\\nIf you’re getting this blue screen repeatedly and you’re worried about your data, our data recovery team can evaluate your drive for free. No obligation, just answers.\\n\\n### What’s in This Guide\\n\\n* What Is the WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR?\\n* Common Causes of This Blue Screen\\n* Step-by-Step Fixes (Start Here)\\n* Advanced Fixes for Persistent Errors\\n* When WHEA Points to a Dying Drive\\n* Protecting Your Data During WHEA Errors\\n* When You Need Professional Data Recovery\\n* Frequently Asked Questions\\n\\n## What Is the WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR?\\n\\nWHEA is a system built into Windows (Vista and later) that monitors hardware components for errors. Your CPU, memory controller, PCIe bus, and storage controllers all report errors through WHEA. Most of the time, WHEA catches and corrects small errors silently in the background. You never even notice.\\n\\nThe blue screen happens when WHEA encounters an error it **cannot** correct. Something has gone wrong at the hardware level, and Windows decides the safest thing to do is stop everything immediately rather than risk data corruption or further damage. That’s what “uncorrectable” means. Windows tried to fix it, failed, and pulled the emergency brake.\\n\\nThe stop code is **0x00000124** .\\nYou’ll usually see it displayed on the blue screen itself, along with the text WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR. Windows 10 and 11 show a sad face emoji and the stop code. Older versions show the classic wall of white text on blue.\\n\\n**Quick context:** Not every blue screen means hardware failure. Driver crashes, software conflicts, and Windows Update bugs cause blue screens too. But WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR specifically indicates a _hardware_ error. That’s what makes it more serious than your average BSOD.\\n\\n### What Windows Is Actually Telling You\\n\\nWhen you get this BSOD, Windows creates a memory dump file with details about the error: which component failed, the error type, and sometimes a specific error code. Most people never look at these dumps. But tools like [WinDbg from Microsoft](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/windows-hardware/drivers/debugger/) or the free BlueScreenView utility can parse them and tell you exactly which component flagged the error.\\n\\n...\\n\\nSSDs trigger WHEA errors when their internal error correction can’t keep up with the number of failing NAND cells. Check your SSD’s health using the manufacturer’s tool (Samsung Magician, WD Dashboard, Intel Memory and Storage Tool, etc.) or CrystalDiskInfo. If the drive shows high wear levels, low remaining life percentage, or uncorrectable error counts, it’s time to back up and plan a replacement. SSDs tend to fail more abruptly than hard drives, so don’t put it off.\\n\\n### Can I fix WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR without reinstalling Windows?\\n\\nIn most cases, yes. Since the error is hardware-related, reinstalling Windows won’t fix the root cause. A fresh Windows install on a failing hard drive will still produce WHEA errors. Focus on the hardware: check temperatures, test RAM, update drivers, and evaluate your storage drive’s health.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.catdatarecovery.com/jp/data-recovery/fix-whea-uncorrectable-error\",\n      \"title\": \"5つの簡単な方法でWHEAの修正不可能なエラーを解決する CAT Data Recovery https://www.catdatarecovery.com › data-recovery › fix-...\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"Please wait while your request is being verified...\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://thetechylife.com/what-causes-whea_uncorrectable_error\",\n      \"title\": \"Unraveling the Mystery of WHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR: Causes, Symptoms, and Solutions\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2025-12-19\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"Skip to content\\n\\n[TheTechyLife](https://thetechylife.com/)\\n\\n[Home](https://thetechylife.com) » [Tech Tips](https://thetechylife.com/tech-tips/) » Unraveling the Mystery of WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR: Causes, Symptoms, and Solutions\\n\\n# Unraveling the Mystery of WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR: Causes, Symptoms, and Solutions\\n\\nDecember 19, 2025 by [John Elmore](https://thetechylife.com/author/john/ \\\"View all posts by John Elmore\\\")\\n\\nThe WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR is a type of Blue Screen of Death (BSOD) error that occurs when a hardware error is detected, and the system is unable to recover from it. This error can be caused by a variety of factors, including hardware failures, driver issues, and system configuration problems. In this article, we will delve into the causes, symptoms, and solutions of the WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR, providing readers with a comprehensive understanding of this complex issue.\\n\\n## Understanding WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR\\nThe WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR is a critical error that occurs when the Windows Hardware Error Architecture (WHEA) detects an uncorrectable hardware error. WHEA is a framework that allows the operating system to detect and handle hardware errors, such as memory errors, CPU errors, and other hardware failures. When an uncorrectable error is detected, the system will typically display a blue screen with an error message, indicating that the system has encountered a critical failure.\\n\\n### Causes Of WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR\\n\\nThere are several causes of the WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR, including:\\n\\nOverheating of the system, which can cause hardware components to fail or malfunction. **Inspecting the cooling system and ensuring proper airflow** can help prevent overheating.  \\nFaulty or failing hardware components, such as RAM, CPU, or motherboard. **Running diagnostic tests** can help identify faulty hardware.  \\nDriver issues, such as outdated or corrupted drivers.\\n**Updating drivers to the latest version** can help resolve driver-related issues.  \\nSystem configuration problems, such as incorrect BIOS settings or conflicting hardware. **Checking the BIOS settings and ensuring that all hardware components are compatible** can help resolve system configuration issues.  \\nPower supply issues, such as a failing power supply or inadequate power delivery. **Checking the power supply and ensuring that it is sufficient for the system** can help prevent power-related issues.\\n\\n### Symptoms Of WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR\\n\\nThe symptoms of the WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR can vary, but common symptoms include:\\n\\nA blue screen with an error message indicating that the system has encountered a critical failure.  \\nThe system crashing or freezing, often with no warning.  \\nThe system restarting repeatedly, with no opportunity to save work or data.  \\nError messages indicating that the system has detected a hardware error or failure.\\n\\n...\\n\\nRemember, **prevention is key** , and regular maintenance can help prevent issues before they become critical.\\n\\n## What Is WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR And How Does It Affect My Computer?\\n\\nThe WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR is a type of Blue Screen of Death (BSOD) error that occurs when a hardware error is detected by the Windows Hardware Error Architecture (WHEA). This error is usually caused by a critical failure in the system’s hardware, such as a malfunctioning CPU, memory, or other components. When this error occurs, the system will automatically shut down to prevent any further damage to the hardware or data loss. The error message will typically display a stop code, which can be used to diagnose the root cause of the problem.\\n\\nIn most cases, the WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR is a sign of a serious hardware issue that needs to be addressed immediately.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.ninjaone.com/blog/how-to-fix-whea-uncorrectable-error-in-windows-11\",\n      \"title\": \"How to Fix \\\"WHEA_Uncorrectable_Error\\\" in Windows 11\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2026-02-24\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"Open the **Event Viewer** and clear existing **WHEA-Logger** entries to start with a clean baseline.\\n3. Run your chosen stress tests to load CPU, memory, and storage.\\n4. Check **Event Viewer** periodically and confirm that no new WHEA events appear during or after testing.\\n\\n## ⚠️ Things to look out for\\n\\n|**Risks** |**Potential Consequences** |**Reversals** |\\n| --- | --- | --- |\\n|Outdated firmware remains in use. |Hardware faults may persist even after other repairs have been made. |Apply the latest BIOS or UEFI update and retest system stability. |\\n|Stress tests generate new WHEA events. |Underlying instability was not resolved by earlier steps. |Re-evaluate CPU, memory, and storage diagnostics and replace failing components |\\n|Overclock settings remain active. |Voltage or frequency instability continues to trigger hardware faults. |Disable all overclocks, restore defaults, and confirm settings persist across reboots. |\\n## Troubleshooting WHEA uncorrectable error code on Windows 11 persistence\\n\\nUse these checks to pinpoint why WHEA events continue after initial repairs.\\n\\n* **WHEA persists after update:** Test RAM and storage hardware to confirm components are not failing under load.\\n* **WHEA Uncorrectable Error occurs under heavy load:** CPU instability is likely in such cases. Remove overclock settings and retest.\\n* **WHEA uncorrectable error occurs during gaming:** Update GPU drivers and verify PCIe bus stability with stress or diagnostics tools.\\n* **Happens after sleep or resume:** Update chipset, power management, and storage firmware to address instability.\\n* **Frequent events with no clear device:** Motherboard voltage regulation issues might be present and require board-level diagnostics.\\n\\n## Restore stability by fixing the WHEA Uncorrectable Error\\n\\nThe WHEA Uncorrectable Error signals a hardware fault that Windows cannot recover from.\\nBy identifying the failing component, updating firmware, correcting overclock settings, and validating system behavior with diagnostics, most issues can be resolved without replacing the entire system.\\n\\n**Related topics:**\\n\\n* How to Update BIOS on Your Windows PC\\n* How to Detect and Analyze Blue Screens of Death (BSOD) with PowerShell\\n* IT Guide: How to Run BSOD Troubleshooter in Windows 10\\n* How to Debug Crash Dumps using WinDbg in Windows 10\\n* How to Enable or Disable BSOD Automatic Restart in Windows\\n\\nStart your Free Trial\\n\\nEmbracing Automation at Every Level\\n\\n## FAQs\\n\\n### What is the most common cause of WHEA Uncorrectable Error?\\n\\nMost cases trace back to unstable CPU or memory behavior. This is often due to failing hardware, outdated firmware, or residual overclock settings. ### Why does the WHEA error only appear under heavy load?\\n\\nHigh load exposes marginal instability in the CPU, RAM, or PCIe bus. Stress tests help reproduce these conditions and confirm the failing component.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.visioncomputers.com/bad-whea-uncorrectable-error\",\n      \"title\": \"WHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR - Fix Guide | Vision Computers | Vision Computers\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2026-03-10\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"Then restart and enter BIOS (Del / F2 / F10) → Load Optimized Defaults → Save & Exit.\\n\\n**Talk to a tech in 15 seconds:**\\n\\nCall 770-840-9249 Toll-Free 800-886-4466 ✉ info@visioncomputers.com ✉ Request Service Online\\n\\nExpert BSOD diagnosis • Hardware fault & overclocking diagnosis\\n\\n5-Star Google\\n\\n5,200+ reviews\\n\\n★★★★★\\n\\n5-Star Trustpilot\\n\\n7,030+ reviews\\n\\n★★★★★\\n\\n100,000+ Customers\\n\\nServed since 1992\\n\\nEst. 1991\\n\\nExpert Diagnosis\\n\\nHardware fault & overclocking diagnosis\\n\\nProfessional\\n\\n## What Causes WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR?\\n\\nWHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR (0x00000124) is triggered when Windows Hardware Error Architecture detects an uncorrectable hardware fault. These are the most common causes:\\n\\n### CPU or memory overclocking\\n\\nOverclocking pushes hardware beyond stable tolerances, causing hardware error signals. Reset BIOS to defaults as the very first step — this is the most common fixable cause of this error.\\n\\n### Overheating CPU or GPU\\nThermal stress creates hardware errors. If the CPU or GPU cannot dissipate heat fast enough under load, it generates hardware errors that WHEA reports. Check temperatures with HWMonitor.\\n\\n### Failing RAM module\\n\\nBad memory causes uncorrectable hardware errors that bubble up through WHEA. Test with Windows Memory Diagnostic to isolate a faulty RAM stick.\\n\\n### Outdated BIOS / firmware\\n\\nAn old BIOS may mishandle hardware error reporting, causing false positives or real errors it can't recover from. Update BIOS from the motherboard manufacturer's website.\\n\\n### Failing CPU or system board\\n\\nIn persistent cases after all other fixes, the CPU itself or a PCH component may be failing. This requires professional diagnosis and stress testing to confirm.\\n\\n**⚠ Important:** Some steps below involve BIOS flashing and hardware testing. A BIOS update interrupted mid-flash can brick your motherboard.\\nIf you are not comfortable with these steps, **do not attempt them** — call our tech support line at 770-840-9249 and we will walk you through it or test the hardware in-store.\\n\\n## How to Fix WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR\\n\\nWork through these steps in order. Most cases are resolved by the first two steps. Only proceed to later steps if the error persists:\\n\\n### Reset BIOS to Default (Disable Overclocking)\\n\\nRestart your computer and press **Del** , **F2** , or **F10** during POST to enter BIOS setup (the key varies by manufacturer — watch the screen on startup). Find **Load Optimized Defaults** or **Load Setup Defaults** (usually under the Exit or Tools menu), then Save and Exit. This is the single most effective first step and resolves overclocking-related WHEA errors permanently.\\n\\n### Check System Temperatures\\n\\nDownload and run **HWMonitor** (free from CPUID). Monitor CPU temperature at idle and under load (run a demanding application or stress test for 5 minutes).\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://linustechtips.com/topic/1440210-whea-uncorrectable-error\",\n      \"title\": \"Whea Uncorrectable Error - Troubleshooting\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2022-06-29\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"com%2Ftopic%2F1440210-whea-uncorrectable-error%2F%3Fdo%3DfindComment%26comment%3D15459738&title=Whea+Uncorrectable+Error \\\"Share on Reddit\\\")\\n\\n* * *\\n\\nMore sharing options...\\n\\n- [](https://linustechtips.com/profile/313534-windows7ge/ \\\"Go to Windows7ge's profile\\\") [](https://linustechtips.com/profile/313534-windows7ge/badges/)\\n* ### **[Windows7ge](https://linustechtips.com/profile/313534-windows7ge/ \\\"Go to Windows7ge's profile\\\")**\\n* Member\\n* Writer of Guides & Tutorials\\n    + [12\\\\.3k](https://linustechtips.com/profile/313534-windows7ge/content/ \\\"12,308 posts\\\")\\n    + [255](https://linustechtips.com/profile/313534-windows7ge/solutions/ \\\"255 solutions\\\")\\n\\n[](https://linustechtips.com/index.php?app=awards&module=awards&controller=awards&do=info&award=4773) [](https://www.boincstats.com/stats/-1/user/detail/73865194514/overview)\\n\\n[](https://linustechtips.com/index.php?app=awards&module=awards&controller=awards&do=info&award=7093)\\n\\n[](https://linustechtips.com/index.php?\\napp=awards&module=awards&controller=awards&do=info&award=7229) [](https://folding.extremeoverclocking.com/user_summary.php?s=&u=1294415)\\n\\n[](https://linustechtips.com/index.php?app=awards&module=awards&controller=awards&do=info&award=7560)\\n\\n[Posted June 29, 2022](https://linustechtips.com/topic/1440210-whea-uncorrectable-error/?do=findComment&comment=15459750)\\n\\n* [](https://linustechtips.com/topic/1440210-whea-uncorrectable-error/ \\\"Share this post\\\")\\n\\nUsually WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR is associated with a hardware failure. This could be an issue with your PSU, GPU, Motherboard, etc.\\n\\nJust from my experience dealing with this error in the past I'd try a different PSU first but you can try pulling sticks of RAM if you want to test something easier. I wouldn't put my trust in whatever Windows memory check is. Most people use MemTestx86 for memory testing and even then there's no guarantee the memory error will propagate on the first go around.\\nMultiple runs might be required so I'll often just pull a stick at a time and see if the system becomes stable again. Faster. Just as easy.\\n\\n**Guides & Tutorials:**\\n\\n[PROXMOX - Rebuilding ZFS RAID rpool After Disk Failure](https://linustechtips.com/topic/1535985-proxmox-rebuilding-zfs-raid-rpool-after-disk-failure/)\\n\\n[Mass Deploying Customized Windows 10/11 Installs](https://linustechtips.com/topic/1531766-mass-deploying-customized-windows-1011-installs/)\\n\\n[Building a GNU/Linux Based Windows Deployment Server](https://linustechtips.com/topic/1482112-building-a-gnulinux-based-windows-deployment-server/)\\n\\n[GNU/Linux Installer Server: Installation & Configuration](https://linustechtips.com/topic/1445036-gnulinux-installer-server-installation-configuration/)\\n\\n[How to: Use (i)PXE to Install Windows from a Network](https://linustechtips.com/topic/1441143-how-to-use-ipxe-to-install-windows-from-a-network/)\\n\\n[Why Memorize IP's When You Can Self-Host DNS Instead?](https://linustechtips.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.ubackup.com/jp/articles/whea-uncorrectable-error-windows-10.html\",\n      \"title\": \"5つの解決策：WHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERRORエラー ubackup.com https://www.ubackup.com › 記事\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2023-04-11\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"* ストア\\n* 製品\\n  \\n  #### AOMEI Backupper スタンドアロン型Windowsバックアップ、クローン、同期ソフト\\n  \\n  家庭向け\\n  \\n  #### AOMEI Backupper Standard\\n  \\n  無料\\n  \\n  個人データを保護するWindowsバックアップフリーソフト\\n  \\n   #### AOMEI Backupper Professional\\n  \\n  個人用Windows PCバックアップ、同期、クローンソフト\\n  \\n  \\n  \\n  ビジネス向け\\n  \\n  #### AOMEI Backupper Workstation\\n  \\n  ビジネス用Windows PCバックアップ、同期、クローンソフト\\n  \\n   #### AOMEI Backupper Server\\n  \\n  頼もしいWindows Serverバックアップ、同期、クローンソリューション\\n  \\n   #### AOMEI Backupper Technician\\n  \\n  社内のパソコン台数無制限のバックアップ、クローンツールキット\\n  \\n   #### AOMEI Backupper Technician Plus\\n  \\n  社内のパソコンとサーバー台数無制限のバックアップ、クローンツールキット\\n  \\n  \\n  \\n  各エディションの違いを理解し、自分に合ったものを選びましょう。 各エディションの比較 >>\\n  \\n  #### AOMEI Backupper Mac スタンドアロン型Macバックアップ、同期ソフト\\n  \\n  #### AOMEI Cyber Backup 集中化 VM、Windows、MSSQL for Businessを集中的にバックアップ\\n  \\n  #### AOMEI Cyber Backup Free\\n  \\n  基本的な企業バックアップと復元のためのバックアップフリーソフト\\n  \\n   #### AOMEI Cyber Backup Premium\\n  \\n  高度な機能で、すべての重要な企業データを無制限のデバイスにバックアップ\\n  \\n  \\n  \\n  #### FoneBackup iPhoneバックアップ、転送フリーソフト\\n  \\n  #### FastRecovery WindowsおよびiOSから紛失または削除されたファイルを復旧\\n* ダウンロード\\n#### AOMEI Backupper 無料ダウンロードでWindowsのバックアップ、同期、クローンを行う #### AOMEI Cyber Backup 無料ダウンロードで企業データを保護 #### FoneBackup 無料ダウンロードでiPhoneデータをバックアップや転送 #### FastRecovery 無料ダウンロードで失われたまたは削除されたデータを復旧\\n* サポート\\n\\n* [アカウント](https://account.aomeitech.com/)\\n* |\\n* \\n\\nAOMEI Backupper\\n\\nオールラウンドなWindows PCデータバックアップ、同期、クローンソフトウェア\\n\\n無料ダウンロード Windows 11/10/8.1/8/7\\n\\nTrustpilot 4.7/5\\n\\n1. AOMEI Backupper >\\n2. 記事 >\\n3. 5つの解決策：WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERRORエラー\\n\\n# 5つの解決策：WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERRORエラー\\n\\nPCを使用していると「停止コード：WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR」のブルースクリーン（BSoD）が突然発生するケースがあります。この記事では、「WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR」のブルースクリーンエラーが発生した時の対処方法について詳しく紹介します。\\n\\nAkira\\n\\nBy [Akira](https://www.ubackup.com/jp/author/akira.html \\\"https://www.ubackup.com/jp/author/akira.html's personal page.\\\") 最終更新日\\n2023年04月11日\\n\\n共有： facebook twitter instagram reddit\\n\\n## 実例：WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERRORエラー\\n\\n[](https://www.ubackup.com/assets/images/posts/0/icon-0.png)\\n\\nPCを起動すると、ブルースクリーンが表示され、エラーはWHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERRORです。システムはエラー情報を収集するブルースクリーンのままですが、プロセスが0％を超えることはなく、システムをリセットする必要があります。この問題を解決する方法はありますか？ありがどうございます。\\n\\n\\\\- ユーザーからの質問\\n\\n[エラー](https://www.ubackup.\\ncom/screenshot/jp/others/whea-uncorrectable-error-windows-10/whea-uncorrectable-error.png \\\"エラー\\\")\\n\\n## WHEA \\\\_ UNCORRECTABLE \\\\_ ERRORの原因\\n\\nWHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERRORのブルースクリーンエラーは、主にハードウェアに問題が起きた際に発生します。具体的には以下のような原因が考えられます。\\n\\n    **ハードウェアの破損** ：メモリ、マザーボード、ハードドライブ、グラフィックカード、その他のハードウェアが損傷しているか、プロセッサの電圧が低すぎるため、オーバークロックや非効率的な冷却システムによってCPUが過熱し、エラーが発生します。\\n    **ドライバの競合** ：誤って構成されたドライバや古いドライバは、システムの競合を引き起こす可能性があります。これは、ドライバの更新またはWindows 10の不適切なアップグレード（ダウングレード）の後に発生する可能性があります。\\n    **システムファイルまたはレジストリーの破損** ：システムファイルまたはレジストリーの破損により、このエラーが発生する可能性があります。これは、ディスクの読み取り／書き込みエラーが原因である可能性があります。\\n\\n## WHEA \\\\_ UNCORRECTABLE \\\\_ ERRORエラーの解決策\\n\\nWindows 10のWHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERRORエラーの原因を理解したので、これらの効果的な解決策に従ってこのエラーを修正できます。\\n\\n### 方法 1. Windows10メモリ診断を実行する\\n\\nPCのハードウェアに障害が発生すると、Windows 10のWHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERRORエラーがが表示されます。したがって、セーフモードを有効にしてシステムに入ることができ、Windows10メモリ診断ツールを使用してメモリの問題を確認できます。\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.securedatarecovery.com/blog/whea-uncorrectable-error\",\n      \"title\": \"How to Fix WHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR BSOD Secure Data Recovery https://www.securedatarecovery.com › ...\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2026-02-19\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"* Home\\n  \\n  >\\n* Blog\\n  \\n  >\\n* How to Fix WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR\\n\\n# How to Fix the WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR BSOD on Windows\\n\\nPosted by\\n\\nYevgeniy Reznik\\n\\nPublished:\\n\\nJun 20, 2025\\n\\nReviewed by\\n\\nUpdated:\\n\\nFeb 19, 2026\\n\\nmin. read\\n\\nTable of Contents\\n\\nGet the Latest News\\n\\nSign-up Success!\\n\\nPlease enter a valid email\\n\\nThe WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR is a specific type of blue screen of death (BSOD) that appears on Windows 10 and Windows 11 systems when the operating system detects a critical hardware issue. It’s triggered by the Windows Hardware Error Architecture (WHEA) — a built-in system that monitors for hardware problems and reports when a component, such as the CPU, GPU, RAM, or motherboard, encounters a failure it cannot recover from. While it can be unsettling to see your device crash unexpectedly, this stop code is designed to protect your system from further damage by halting operations safely.\\nIn most cases, the underlying cause of this error is related to hardware instability. This could mean overheating, misconfigured BIOS or UEFI settings, faulty device drivers, or hardware that’s beginning to show signs of wear. However, not all causes are strictly hardware-based. The error can also stem from critical system files and firmware-level software that manage how Windows interacts with your hardware. Corruption in these layers, or conflicts introduced by recent Windows updates, firmware changes, or overclocking, can all contribute to the WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR.\\n\\nWhile some users are able to troubleshoot this issue successfully on their own, others may find that the error recurs or prevents normal startup. If valuable data is stored on the affected computer, it’s essential to proceed cautiously. Running stress tests or reinstalling Windows without a backup can sometimes make data recovery more difficult.\\nThat’s why it can be helpful to consult professionals who are equipped to assess both the hardware issue and the safety of your data.\\n\\nIf you’re experiencing this error and want to avoid unnecessary risk, [**Secure Data Recovery**](https://www.securedatarecovery.com/) offers expert support for systems affected by hardware-related crashes. Our specialists can perform in-depth diagnostics, recover data from affected drives, and help you move forward with confidence.\\n\\nWhat is the WHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR?\\n\\n## Underlying causes behind the error (and what to do next)\\n\\nWhile the WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR may seem sudden, it’s typically the result of an underlying issue that has developed over time. These causes can range from minor software conflicts to more serious hardware failures. To help you better understand what might be happening behind the scenes, we’ve outlined the most common causes below, along with common symptoms to help you diagnose the issue.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://couldask.com/en/guides/tech/oswindows/how-to-fix-whea-uncorrectable-error\",\n      \"title\": \"How to Fix WHEA Uncorrectable Error in Windows 10/11\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"Sunday, June 28\\n\\nTheme\\n\\nEN ▾\\n\\n[Русский](https://couldask.com/ru/kak-ispravit-oshibku-whea-uncorrectable-error) [English](https://couldask.com/en/how-to-fix-whea-uncorrectable-error)\\n\\n🏠 Home Sections: All 📖 Guides 🔧 Fixes 💡 Concepts ⚖️ Compare 🛠️ Tools Справка\\n\\n×\\n\\n#### Help\\n\\nUse the search bar to find error codes or manuals. Articles are categorized in the top menu.\\n\\nSubcategories: Back All Adults Contact Excel Git Google Mail Media Windows More 7 ▾\\n\\n### Select Subcategory\\n\\n×\\n\\nHome / Guides / IT & Tech / Windows\\n\\nIT & Tech\\n\\n# How to Fix WHEA Uncorrectable Error in Windows 10/11\\n\\nCouldAsk Editorial 27\\\\.06.2026 2 min 👁️ 139\\n\\nQuick Solution\\n\\nError 0x00000124 is a critical hardware failure (overheating, overclocking, or power issues). Key steps: reset BIOS to factory defaults, disable overclocking, and check system files and disk integrity.\\nBlue screen of death with WHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR and stop code 0x00000124 on a computer monitor The **WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR** (stop code `0x00000124` ) is a critical failure of the Windows Hardware Error Architecture. Unlike many other Blue Screen of Death (BSoD) errors, this one indicates a hardware issue in 90% of cases, rather than a software glitch.\\n\\n## Main Causes of the Error\\n\\nThe system protects itself to prevent physical damage to the components. The primary culprits are:\\n\\n* Overheating of the processor (CPU) or graphics card (GPU).\\n* Unstable overclocking or enabled XMP profiles for RAM.\\n* A faulty power supply unit (PSU) causing voltage spikes.\\n* Physical wear and tear of the system drive (SSD/HDD).\\n\\n## Step-by-Step Solution\\n\\n### Step 1: Disable Overclocking\\n\\nIf you have overclocked your CPU or RAM, revert to the base settings.\\n1\\\\. Restart your computer and enter the BIOS/UEFI (usually by pressing `Del` or `F2` ).\\n2\\\\.\\nFind the **Load Optimized Defaults** option or manually reset the CPU and RAM frequency settings (disable XMP).\\n3\\\\. Save the changes ( `F10` ) and reboot.\\n\\n⚠️ Before updating or resetting the BIOS, ensure your computer is connected to a reliable power source (ideally through a UPS). A sudden power outage while working in the BIOS can brick your motherboard.\\n\\n### Step 2: Check System Files and Disk\\n\\nIf the BIOS is reset but the error persists, check the integrity of the file system.\\nOpen the Command Prompt as an Administrator and type the following commands one by one:\\n\\n* `chkdsk /f /r` (requires a reboot to scan the disk).\\n* `sfc /scannow` (system file check).\\n\\nℹ️ Pro Tip\\n\\nThe WHEA error often occurs after installing new RAM sticks. If you recently upgraded your memory, try removing the modules, wiping the contacts with a regular eraser, and pushing them back in until you hear a distinct click.\\n\\n## Recommended Reading\\n\\nFor an in-depth analysis of BSoD causes, I recommend studying:\"\n      ]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"warnings\": null,\n  \"usage\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"sku_search\",\n      \"count\": 1\n    }\n  ],\n  \"session_id\": \"ses_0d4353da7ffeYcDQulSCL0yoGQ\"\n}",
