    {
      "type": "answer",
      "text": "Now let me check thermal data, HP BIOS update status, and look deeper at the memory pressure issue.",
      "timestamp": 1783146439725
    },
    {
      "type": "thought",
      "text": "Key findings so far:\n\n1. **System**: HP OMEN Laptop 15-ce0xx,16GB RAM, Windows 10 Pro Build 19045\n2. **CPU**: Intel (7th gen, since it's a 15-ce0xx model) - need more info\n3. **GPU**: Intel HD Graphics 630 + NVIDIA GeForce GTX 1050\n4. **Storage**: HGST 1TB HDD + ADATA SX6000NP 512GB NVMe SSD\n5. **BIOS**: AMI BIOS version 40.28\n6. **Motherboard**: HP 838F\n\nKey observations from event logs:\n- **No WHEA-Logger events found** in the event log - this is significant\n- **No BSOD minidumps** in C:\\Windows\\Minidump\n- Multiple **Kernel-Power Event105** entries (power transitions)\n- Multiple **\"insufficient virtual memory\"** warnings - Chrome using 3.5GB, vmmem (Hyper-V) using 1.1GB, opencode.exe using 827MB\n- Event ID **1796** and **1801** errors (memory-related)\n- **Intel DPTF** (Dynamic Platform and Thermal Framework) events - esif_uf.exe process- Multiple service errors (7000, 7009) at boot\n\nThe fact that there are NO WHEA-Logger events in the system log but the user got a WHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR BSOD is interesting. This could mean:\n1. The BSOD happened and the dump wasn't written properly\n2. The error was severe enough that Windows couldn't log it3. The minidumps were cleaned up\n\nThe repeated \"insufficient virtual memory\" warnings are a significant finding - the system is running out of RAM and heavily using pagefile. With16GB RAM, Chrome consuming 3.5GB, Hyper-V using 1.1GB, and opencode using 827MB, plus other processes, the system could be memory-starved.\n\nThe Intel DPTF (Dynamic Platform and Thermal Framework) events suggest thermal management is active, which is relevant to temperature concerns.\n\nLet me also check:\n- HP BIOS version against latest available\n- Thermal throttling history\n- Driver versions\n- Pagefile configuration",
      "timestamp": 1783146455334
    },
    {
