      "output": "{\n  \"search_id\": \"search_226e4d1150ff439484ea85cd071769fa\",\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://drivers.softpedia.com/get/BIOS/HP/HP-OMEN-15-ce000-BIOS-F-17-for-Windows-10-64-bit.shtml\",\n      \"title\": \"Download HP OMEN 15-ce000 BIOS F.17 for Windows 10 64 bit | Softpedia\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2018-11-06\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"SOFTPEDIA®\\n    *   Windows Apps\\n    *   Mac Apps\\n    *   Linux Apps\\n    *   Drivers\\n    *   Android APK\\n    *   Reviews\\n\\n    *     *     * \\n\\nSoftpedia > Drivers > BIOS > HP >   HP OMEN 15-ce000 BIOS F.17 for Windows 10 64-bit\\nGO\\nDOWNLOAD : HP OMEN 15-ce000 BIOS F.17 for Windows 10 64-bit\\nGO\\nHP OMEN 15-ce000 BIOS F.17 for Windows 10 64-bit\\nManufacturer: HP Date:\\nNov 6, 2018\\nSOFTPEDIA® DOWNLOAD NOW 3,218 downloads\\nDescription\\nDOWNLOAD NOW\\nThis package provides a tool to update the firmware for the supported computer models that are running a supported operating system.\\nChanges:\\n- Provides improved system stability. - Provides enhanced security. NOTE: HP strongly recommends transitioning promptly to this updated BIOS version which supersedes all previous releases. If it has been installed, updating (overwrite-installing) may fix problems, add new functions, or expand existing ones.\\nEven though other OSes might be compatible as well, we do not recommend applying this release on platforms other than the ones specified. \\nAbout BIOS Update Utility:\\nApplying a new BIOS version can bring various fixes, add new features, or improve existing ones; however, this action is very risky and should be carefully carried out in a steady power environment (such as the one ensured by a UPS unit), and only when it is really needed. Moreover, it is recommended that the BIOS be upgraded by someone who has the ability to use advanced system features. It can also be fulfilled by a regular user as well, but at their own risk. The Basic Input/Output System (BIOS) is a highly important piece of software that loads the currently installed operating system and tests all hardware components – so make sure you flash it correctly.\\nWhen it comes to changing the BIOS version, the update utility searches for a compatible package in any given location or on the web and, if found, it will automatically install the desired build, if and when your approval is given. Do take into account that failing to perform the installation could seriously damage your system, and the faulty BIOS might even render it unusable. Therefore, if you intend to upgrade your BIOS, hit the download button, get and install the package, and run the utility to check if a newer version is available. Don't forget to check with our website as often as possible to be up to date with the latest releases.\\nDOWNLOAD HP OMEN 15-ce000 BIOS F.17 for Windows 10 64-bit\\nFiled under\\nHP OMEN 15 BIOS HP OMEN 15 BIOS Update HP OMEN 15-ce000 BIOS Update OMEN 15-ce000 BIOS HP BIOS Update\\n    *   CATEGORY:\\n    * BIOS\\n    *   COMPATIBLE WITH:\\n    * Windows 10 64 bit\\n    *   file size:\\n    * 9.6 MB\\n    *   filename:\\n    * sp88698.exe\\n\\n \\ni softpedia®\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://h30434.www3.hp.com/t5/Desktop-Boot-and-Lockup/BIOS-Update/td-p/9466399\",\n      \"title\": \"\\n\\tBIOS Update - HP Support Community - 9466399\\n\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2025-08-28\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"I have an OMEN 25L Desktop GT12-0xxx (product number 7WM96AV, latest windows 11 install) with an 8704 motherboard that has BIOS version F.23 installed.  I have attempted to enable XMP profiles and set custom profile settings after installing CORSAIR - VENGEANCE LPX 64GB (2PK x 32GB) 3200MHz DDR4 C16 DIMM Desktop Memory.  Whenever I attempt to enable any XMP settings in BIOS, none work although the RAM supports it.  I understand HP motherboards only like specific RAM to allow for XMP settings so this is why I attempted to activate it through custom settings but have not been able to.\\n\\nWhile I have been working through this issue, I discovered HP Support Assistant is indicating there is a BIOS update from F.23 to F.28 (sp155344).  I have attempted to install this BIOS update but the installation consistently fails (installer just disappears midway through) and triggers the corrupt BIOS fixer back to F.23.\\nI am attempting to find out how I can successfully update my BIOS and if in doing so, this allows me to successfully apply XMP settings now?  Thanks in advance.\\n\\nTags (1)\\n\\n* Tags:\\n* OMEN 25L Desktop GT12-0xxx\\n\\nView All (1)\\n\\n[I have the same question](https://h30434.www3.hp.com/t5/forums/v4/forumtopicpage.externalratingdisplay.ratingenumerationdisplay.link:rating/rating-enum/0/rating-system/forum_topic_metoo/message-uid/9466399?t:ac=board-id/lockups/thread-id/86719&t:cp=ratings/contributionpage&ticket=bi4MNNZxXMLA_-1)\\n\\n5 REPLIES 5\\n\\nGarp_senchau\\n\\nRetired [Garp\\\\_senchau](https://h30434.www3.hp.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/8689955)\\n\\n10,188 461 564 1,400\\n\\nRetired\\n\\n‎08-22-2025 03:12 PM\\n\\nHP Recommended\\n\\n* Mark as New\\n* Bookmark\\n* Subscribe\\n* \\n* Permalink\\n* Print\\n* \\n* Flag Post\\n\\n@mitch757 , Welcome to HP Support Community,\\n\\nThank you for posting your query; I’m here to help by guiding you through steps to resolve this issue\\n\\n**Find the correct BIOS for your model**\\nGo to HP's website: support.hp.com\\n\\nSearch your **product number: 7WM96AV**\\n\\nDownload the latest BIOS version made **specifically for OMEN 25L GT12 with SSID 8704**\\n\\n**BIOS Recovery**\\n\\nKindly refer to this guide to perform the recovery: [HP Notebook PCs - Recovering the BIOS (Basic Input Output System) | HP® Support](https://support.hp.com/in-en/document/ish_3932413-2337994-16)\\n\\nI hope this helps.\\n\\nPlease feel free to reply here if you have any questions or if you need further clarification on any of the steps.\\n\\nTake care and have a good day.\\n\\nDid we resolve the issue? If yes, please consider marking this post as \\\" **Accepted Solution** \\\" and click \\\" **Yes** \\\" to give us a helpful vote - your feedback keeps us going!\\n\\nRegards,\\n\\n**Garp\\\\_Senchau**  \\nI am an HP Employee\\n\\nWas this reply helpful? [Yes](https://h30434.www3.hp.com/t5/forums/v4/forumtopicpage.externalratingdisplay.ratingenumerationdisplay.link:rating/rating-enum/1/rating-system/medaltesttest/message-uid/946809\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://support.hp.com/id-en/document/ish_5894090-5894156-16/hpsbhf03779\",\n      \"title\": \"AMI UEFI Firmware March 2022 Security Updates | HP® Support\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"exe> |\\n|HP Pavilion 15-bc5xx |BIOS |F.15 |Rev 1 |SP134419 |<https://ftp.hp.com/pub/softpaq/sp134001-134500/sp134419.exe> |\\n|HP Pavilion 15-cd0xx, 15z-cd000 |BIOS |F.30 |Rev 1 |SP135720 |<https://ftp.hp.com/pub/softpaq/sp135501-136000/sp135720.exe> |\\n|HP Pavilion 15-cw0xxx, 15z-cw000 |BIOS |F.47 |Rev 1 |SP134485 |<https://ftp.hp.com/pub/softpaq/sp134001-134500/sp134485.exe> |\\n|HP Pavilion 15-cw1xxx, 15z-cw100 |BIOS |F.47 |Rev 1 |SP134485 |<https://ftp.hp.com/pub/softpaq/sp134001-134500/sp134485.exe> |\\n|HP Pavilion 15-dp0xx |BIOS |F.11 |Rev 1 |SP134420 |<https://ftp.hp.com/pub/softpaq/sp134001-134500/sp134420.exe> |\\n|HP Pavilion 17-ab4xxx |BIOS |F.31 |Rev 1 |SP134418 |<https://ftp.hp.com/pub/softpaq/sp134001-134500/sp134418.exe> |\\n|HP Pavilion 17-ar0xxx, 17z-ar000 |BIOS |F.30 |Rev 1 |SP135720 |<https://ftp.hp.com/pub/softpaq/sp135501-136000/sp135720.exe> |\\n|HP Spectre x360 13-ae0xx, 13-ae5xx, 13t-ae000 |BIOS |F.35 |Rev 1 |SP132892 |<https://ftp.hp.\\ncom/pub/softpaq/sp132501-133000/sp132892.exe> |\\n|HP Spectre x360 13-ap0xxx, 13t-ap000 |BIOS |F.44 |Rev 1 |sp128629 |<https://ftp.hp.com/pub/softpaq/sp128501-129000/sp128629.exe> |\\n|HP Spectre x360 15-ch0xx |BIOS |F.35 |Rev 1 |SP132893 |<https://ftp.hp.com/pub/s