/services-overview.html)\\n  \\n    + [Support & Troubleshooting Support and troubleshooting image](https://support.hp.com/us-en)\\n    + [Software & Drivers Software and drivers image](https://support.hp.com/us-en/drivers)\\n    + [Check Warranty Check warranty image](https://support.hp.com/us-en/check-warranty)\\n    + [Contact Us Contact us image](https://support.hp.com/us-en/contact)\\n\\n[](https://www.hp.com/us-en/shop/cart)\\n\\n## Your Cart is Empty\\n\\n[](https://www.hp.com/us-en/home.html \\\"HP® Official Site | Laptops, Computers, Desktops , Printers, and more\\\") Skip to Content Skip to Footer\\n\\n \\n\\n* \\n\\nsolution Content\\n\\n# Check for a BIOS update using HP Support Assistant\\n\\nUse HP Support Assistant to check for and install a BIOS update on your computer. When a new BIOS update becomes available,\\nHP Support Assistant can update your computer automatically. HP computers with Windows come with HP Support Assistant (HPSA)\\ninstalled.\\n\\n1.\\nIn Windows, search for and open HP Support Assistant .\\n   \\n   Note:\\n   \\n   If the app is not installed on your computer, go to [HP Support Assistant](http://www.hp.com/go/hpsupportassistant) to download the latest version.\\n2. On the My devices or My notebook tab, select Updates .\\n   \\n   My notebook tab\\n3. If a new BIOS update is available, check the box next the BIOS update and any other updates you want to install, and then\\n   click Download and install .\\n\\n* * *\\n\\n* * *\\n\\n### Additional support options\\n\\nTry one of our automated tools or diagnostics Try one of our automated tools or diagnostics [Ask a question on our HP Support Community page Ask a question on our HP Support Community page](https://h30434.www3.hp.com/ \\\"Ask a question on our HP Support Community page\\\") Get in touch with one of our support agents Get in touch with one of our support agents\\n\\n* * *\\n\\n## Enter a topic to search our knowledge library\\n\\nEnter a topic to search our knowledge library What can we help you with?\\nSearch search image\\n\\nVirtual Assistant Ask our Virtual Assistant Try asking HP's Virtual Assistant.\\n\\nloader\\n\\n## Your Privacy\\n\\nMore Options\\n\\nReject Accept\\n\\nCompany Logo\\n\\n## Privacy Preference Center\\n\\n## Privacy Preference Center\\n\\n* ### Your Privacy\\n* ### Strictly Necessary Cookies\\n* ### Performance & Analytics Cookies\\n* ### Personalization Cookies\\n* ### Targeting Cookies\\n* ### Sell or Share my Personal Data\\n\\n#### Your Privacy\\n\\nWhen you visit any website, it may store or retrieve information on your browser, mostly in the form of cookies. This information might be about you, your preferences or your device and is mostly used to make the site work as you expect it to. The information does not usually directly identify you, but it can give you a more personalized web experience. Because we respect your right to privacy, you can choose not to allow some types of cookies. Click on t\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.windowslatest.com/2026/05/26/hp-admits-its-latest-bios-update-is-bricking-windows-11-with-bitlocker-loop-blocking-secure-boot-2023-fix\",\n      \"title\": \"HP admits its latest BIOS update is bricking Windows 11 with ...\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2026-05-26\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"your username\\n\\nyour password\\n\\nForgot your password? Get help\\n\\nCreate an account\\n\\nCreate an account\\n\\nWelcome! Register for an account\\n\\nyour email\\n\\nyour username\\n\\nA password will be e-mailed to you.\\n\\nPassword recovery\\n\\nRecover your password\\n\\nyour email\\n\\nA password will be e-mailed to you.\\n\\nTrending:\\n\\n* [Remove Recall AI](https://www.windowslatest.com/2025/04/28/disable-remove-recall-feature-in-windows-11/)\\n* [New Start menu](https://www.windowslatest.com/2025/04/04/windows-11s-start-menu-is-getting-a-big-redesign-without-recommended-feed/)\\n* [Windows 11 25H2](https://www.windowslatest.com/2025/04/25/leak-shows-windows-11-25h2-with-build-26200-not-a-big-release-like-windows-11-24h2/)\\n* [New Windows 11 ISO](https://www.windowslatest.com/2024/10/01/download-windows-11-24h2-iso-from-microsoft/)\\n* [Windows 11 24H2](https://www.windowslatest.com/2024/10/01/how-to-install-windows-11-24h2-now-available-for-everyone/)\\n* [Windows 11 AI requirements](https://www.windowslatest.\\ncom/2024/05/20/microsoft-confirms-windows-11-recall-ai-hardware-requirements/)\\n* [Restore WordPad](https://www.windowslatest.com/2024/06/23/you-can-restore-wordpad-in-windows-11-24h2/)\\n\\n[Home](https://www.windowslatest.com/) Windows 11\\n\\n* [Windows 11](https://www.windowslatest.com/windows-11-news/)\\n\\n# HP admits its latest BIOS update is bricking Windows 11 with BitLocker loop, blocking Secure Boot 2023 fix\\n\\nBy\\n\\n[Abhijith M B](https://www.windowslatest.com/author/abhijith/)\\n\\n\\\\-\\n\\nMay 26, 2026\\n\\n[0](https://www.windowslatest.com/2026/05/26/hp-admits-its-latest-bios-update-is-bricking-windows-11-with-bitlocker-loop-blocking-secure-boot-2023-fix/)\\n\\n[HP confirms premium laptops are stuck in BitLocker recovery loops after recent BIOS updates](https://www.windowslatest.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/HP-confirms-premium-laptops-are-stuck-in-BitLocker-recovery-loops-after-recent-BIOS-updates.jpg) HP confirms premium laptops are stuck in BitLocker recovery loops after recent BIOS updates\\nA widespread wave of system failures has struck owners of premium HP commercial laptops, desktops, and high-end workstations. Users who accepted critical firmware updates released by HP in early **April 2026** found their multi-thousand-dollar machines transformed into inoperable hardware or locked inside an unending **BitLocker recovery loops.**\\n\\nFollowing weeks of mounting user complaints, HP officially published a support advisory confirming the flaw. The advisory notes that the bug impacts a huge fleet of corporate hardware, spanning all HP Commercial Notebooks, Commercial Desktops, and Workstation Computers, running **Windows 11 23H2, 24H2, and 25H2** .\\n\\nBitLocker recovery screen\\n\\nAs expected, the issue is incredibly frustrating for end users. After installing the faulty BIOS update, the computer boots directly to a BitLocker recovery screen.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://support.hp.com/us-en/document/ish_9767626-9767684-16\",\n      \"title\": \"HP PCs – OMEN BIOS setup utility information and menu options ...\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"solution Content\\n\\n# HP PCs – OMEN BIOS setup utility information and menu options\\n\\nThe BIOS controls communication between system devices such as the disk drive, display, and keyboard. It also stores configuration\\ninformation, such as information for peripheral types, the startup sequence, and extended memory amounts. Each BIOS version\\nis customized based on the computer hardware configuration, and includes a built-in setup utility to access and change certain\\ncomputer settings.\\n\\n## Update the BIOS\\n\\nUpdating the BIOS is recommended as standard maintenance of the computer. It can also help to resolve specific issues, improve\\ncomputer performance, or provide support for hardware components or Windows upgrades.\\n\\nIf you need to update the BIOS, go to [HP Consumer Desktop PCs - Updating the BIOS (Basic Input Output System) (Windows)](https://support.hp.\\ncom/us-en/document/ish_4129273-2331498-16) or [HP Consumer Notebook PCs - Updating the BIOS (Basic Input Output System) (Windows)](https://support.hp.com/us-en/document/ish_3894564-1633733-16) . You can update the BIOS whether or not Windows starts.\\n\\n## Open OMEN Setup Utility\\n\\nThe OMEN Setup Utility allows you to view security, configuration, boot options. UEFI HII configuration, and other settings\\nfor your gaming laptop or desktop. You must access the OMEN Setup Utility to configure various settings for your gaming laptop\\nor desktop.\\n\\n1. Turn off the computer and wait five seconds.\\n2. Turn on the computer, and then immediately press the esc key repeatedly until the Startup Menu opens.\\n3. Press the appropriate function key to open the OMEN Setup Utility.\\n\\n## Main tab settings\\n\\nThe Main tab in the OMEN Setup Utility shows product information such as product name, number and family, system board ID, BIOS version,\\nand basic specifications.\\n\\nMain tab settings\\n\\n## Security tab settings\\nThe Security tab allows you to set an administrator password and configure TPM settings.\\n\\nNote:\\n\\nHP recommends that you do not set an administrator password.\\n\\nSecurity tab settings\\n\\n## Configuration tab settings (desktops)\\n\\nThe Configuration tab allows you to view the fan speeds and other power-related features, and to enable virtualization.\\n\\nConfiguration tab settings\\n\\n## Configuration tab settings (notebooks)\\n\\nThe Configuration tab allows you to enable virtualization, action keys, the graphics-switching battery optimizer, and other power-related features.\\n\\nConfiguration tab settings (notebooks)\\n\\n## Boot options settings (desktops)\\n\\nThe Boot Options tab allows you to change the boot order and configure other boot options.\\n\\nBoot option settings (desktops)\\n\\n## Boot options settings (notebooks)\\n\\nThe Boot Options tab allows you to change the boot order and configure other boot options.\\n\\nBoot options settings (notebooks)\\n\\n## Advanced settings\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://support.hp.com/us-en/document/ish_4129273-2331498-16\",\n      \"title\": \"HP Consumer Desktop PCs - Updating the BIOS (Basic Input Output System) (Windows) | HP® Support\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"For more information, see [HP PCs - Frequently Asked Questions about Windows in S Mode](https://support.hp.com/us-en/document/ish_6968751-6968809-16) .\\n\\n1. In Windows, search for and open HP Support Assistant , or click the app icon in the taskbar.\\n   \\n   Note:\\n   \\n   Make sure that you are using HP Support Assistant version 8 or later. If this version of the app is not installed on your\\n   computer, download the latest version from the [HP Support Assistant](https://support.hp.com/help/hp-support-assistant) website.\\n2. On the **My Dashboard** tab, find your computer, and then click Updates .\\n3. Wait while HP Support Assistant analyzes the system.\\n4. After the analysis completes, select the listed updates, download and install the updates, and then follow any on-screen instructions.\\n5. If prompted, restart the computer, and then close the tool.\\n\\n## Update the BIOS manually from within Windows\\n\\nYou can manually install a BIOS update when Windows opens and you have internet access.\\n### Gathering the required information about your computer BIOS\\n\\nTo find the correct BIOS update, get the computer product name and number, the motherboard or system board ID (referred to\\nas the 'ROM Family SSID' in the BIOS update name), the BIOS version, and the processor name.\\n\\n1. Press and hold the ctrl and alt keys, and then press the s key to open the HP System Information utility.\\n   \\n   Alternatively, click Start , and then search for and open HP System Information .\\n   \\n   Note:\\n   \\n   For more information, go to [Find product and serial numbers for HP PCs, printers, and accessories](https://support.hp.com/us-en/document/ish_2039298-1862169-16) .\\n   \\n   HP System Information window\\n2. Write down the Product name, Product number, Motherboard ID, BIOS version, and Processor name.\\n\\n### Prepare your computer for the BIOS update\\n\\nTo prevent possible problems, close any open applications, and temporarily disable antivirus software and BitLocker before\\nupdating the BIOS.\\n\\n1.\\nClose any open applications.\\n2. Temporarily disable your antivirus software. In Windows, search for and open Security and Maintenance settings, and then click Security to access virus protection settings.\\n3. Temporarily disable BitLocker drive encryption. In Windows, search for and open Manage Bitlocker . Click Suspend protection , and then click Yes . Be prepared and have the BitLocker recovery key available.\\n   \\n   CAUTION:\\n   \\n   If BitLocker is not disabled, the next time you restart the computer the BitLocker key might not be recognized. If you do\\n   not know the BitLocker recovery key, you might lose data or need to reinstall Windows.\\n   \\n   Suspending BitLocker protection\\n\\n### Install the BIOS update\\n\\nDownload and install a BIOS update from the HP website.\\n\\n1. Go to the [HP Software and Driver Downloads](https://support.hp.com/drivers) page.\\n2. Navigate to the product pag\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://h30434.www3.hp.com/t5/Gaming-Notebooks/hp-omen-15-ce0xx-black-screen-after-bios-update/td-p/7542667\",\n      \"title\": \"\\n\\thp omen 15 ce0xx black screen after bios update. - HP Support Community - 7542667\\n\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2020-04-13\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"* HP Community\\n* \\n* Gaming\\n* \\n* Gaming Notebooks\\n* \\n* hp omen 15 ce0xx black screen after bios update.\\n\\n## hp omen 15 ce0xx black screen after bios update.\\n\\nOptions\\n\\n* Mark Topic as New\\n* Mark Topic as Read\\n* \\n* Float this Topic for Current User\\n* Bookmark\\n* Subscribe\\n* Mute\\n* \\n* Printer Friendly Page\\n\\nEntire Community This Category This Board Knowledge base Users cancel\\n\\n[turn on suggested results](https://h30434.www3.hp.com/t5/forums/v4/forumtopicpage.enableautocomplete:enableautocomplete?t:ac=board-id/GamingNotebooks/thread-id/76350&t:cp=action/contributions/searchactions&ticket=KcIwkhB1eDEY_-1)  Auto-suggest helps you quickly narrow down your search results by suggesting possible matches as you type.\\n\\nShowing results for\\n\\nSearch instead for \\n\\nDid you mean: \\n\\nStart a conversation\\n\\nGuidelines\\n\\nJoin the HP Community Solve‑a‑thon | Help Others & Share Your Solutions | Live on Zoom | 2:30 PM to 2:30 AM IST | Every Wednesday [Click here to know more](https://h30434.www3.hp.\\ncom/t5/Community-Blog/HP-Community-Solve-a-thon-Everyone-s-Welcome/ba-p/9621311)\\n\\n## Create an account on the HP Community to personalize your profile and ask a question\\n\\nYour account also allows you to connect with HP support faster, access a personal dashboard to manage all of your devices in one place, view warranty information, case status and more.\\n\\nSign in / Create an account\\n\\n[Learn more](https://support.hp.com/us-en/help/hp-account?jumpid=in_r11498_us/en/topic/ribbon)\\n\\n / Create an account / [Learn more](https://support.hp.com/us-en/help/hp-account?jumpid=in_r11498_us/en/topic/ribbon)\\n\\nLocked\\n\\nIt has been a while since anyone has replied. Simply ask a new question if you would like to start the discussion again .\\n\\nX10\\n\\n[X10](https://h30434.www3.hp.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/3668685)\\n\\n1 0 0 844\\n\\nNew member\\n\\n‎04-08-2020 03:56 PM \\\\- edited ‎04-08-2020 04:00 PM\\n\\nHP Recommended\\n\\n* Mark as New\\n* Bookmark\\n* Subscribe\\n* \\n* Permalink\\n* Print\\n* \\n* Flag Post\\nProduct: HP omen 15 ceOxx gtx1050\\n\\nOperating System: Microsoft Windows 10 (64-bit)\\n\\nafter updating my computer i turn it off and next day when i open it its all black screen so i plug it in to external monitor and its working . i tryd to reinstall the graphic (nvdia1050) from the device man and restart it didn't work .. so i know i must reset the bios but for the last time i want to update my drive but i accidntaly click the disable and thats where the real problem started the screen went black .  i disassmble the laptop to look for any sign of cmos battery but no cmos nore jumper reset pin.. any help pls..\\n\\nTags (2)\\n\\n* Tags:\\n* HP omen 15 ceOxx gtx1050\\n* Microsoft Windows 10 (64-bit)\\n\\nView All (2)\\n\\n[I have the same question]